Claims Claims 1. A front upper frame connection (270) for a space frame (20) comprising: a top surface (271); a bottom surface (273) opposite the top surface (271); a right-side surface (277); a left-side surface (276) opposite the right-side surface (277) and parallel to the right-side surface (277); a front surface (278); a rear surface (279) opposite the front surface (278); a pair of forward support plates (2710) provided on the front surface (278); a pair of forward flat mounting surfaces (2714); and a pair of rocker attachment interfaces (272) located on the top surface (271) adjacent to the rear surface (279) and respectively the right-side surface (277) and the left-side surface (276), wherein the front surface (278) and the forward support plates (2710) define a cutout section (2700), and wherein each of the forward support plates (2710) is curved such that a first portion is parallel to the rear surface (279) and a second portion is perpendicular to the rear surface (279), the first portion being closer to a transverse centerline of the front upper frame connection (270) than the second portion. 2. The front upper frame connection of claim 1, further comprising: a rear left-side mounting surface (2702) located at a rear of the left-side surface (276); a rear right-side mounting surface (2704) located at a rear of the right-side surface (277); 

 a pair of outer bottom mounting surfaces (2706) located at a rear of the bottom surface (273) and orientated toward the left-side surface (276) and right-side surface (277), respectively; and a pair of inner bottom mounting surfaces (2708) located at the rear of the bottom surface (273) and orientated away from the left-side surface (276) and right-side surface (277), respectively. 3. The front upper frame connection of claim 2, wherein the rear left-side mounting surface (2702) is adapted to weldably attach a cab support frame tube (203), wherein the rear right-side mounting surface (2704) is adapted to weldably attach a horizontal frame support (2750), wherein the outer bottom mounting surfaces (2706) are adapted to weldably attach a pair of front upper frame connections (250), and wherein the inner bottom mounting surfaces (2708) are adapted to weldably attach a pair of angled front frame tubes (207). 4. The front upper frame connection of claim 1, wherein a length of the top surface (271) is greater than a width of the top surface (271) in an overhead plan view of the front upper frame connection (270). 5. The front upper frame connection of claim 1, wherein the forward support plates (2710) are adapted to abut respective front upper suspension connections (280), wherein the forward flat mounting surfaces (2714) are adapted to be respectively fixedly attached to the front upper suspension connections (280), and wherein the rocker attachment interfaces (272) are adapted to be respectively pivotally coupled to support rockers (274). 6. The front upper frame connection of claim 1, wherein the forward support plates (2710) are closer to a transverse centerline of the top surface (271) than the forward flat mounting surfaces (2714). 7. A space frame (20) of a rear haul truck (10) comprising: a front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270) having a top surface (271), a bottom surface (273) opposite the top surface (271), a right-side surface (277), and a left-side surface (276) opposite the right-side surface (277); a pair of support rockers (274) attached to the top surface (271) of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270) via respective rocker attachment interfaces (272) on the top surface (271) of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270); a pair of front upper frame connections (250) attached to the bottom surface (273) of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270) via respective outer bottom mounting surfaces (2706) on the bottom surface (273) of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270); and a pair of angled front frame tubes (207) attached to the bottom surface (273) of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270) via respective inner bottom mounting surfaces (2708) on the bottom surface (273) of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270), wherein the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270) further includes: a pair of forward support plates (2710), a pair of forward flat mounting surfaces (2714), and a cutout section (2700) between the forward support plates (2710). 8. The space frame of claim 7, wherein the forward support plates (2710) are forward of the forward flat mounting surfaces (2714) in a length direction of the space frame (20), the forward flat mounting surfaces (2714) are 

forward of the rocker attachment interfaces (272) in the length direction of the space frame (20), and the rocker attachment interfaces (272) are forward of a rear surface (279) of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270). 9. The space frame of claim 7, wherein the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270) further includes: a rear left-side mounting surface (2702) located at a rear portion of the left-side surface (276); and a rear right-side mounting surface (2704) located at a rear portion of the right-side surface (277). 10. The space frame of claim 7, wherein a length of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270) is greater than a width of the front upper body support and frame connection fabrication (270), the length running in a width direction of the space frame (20).
